data.title: McCormick Center for Early Childhood Leadership
data.text:
Aim4Excellence

Links to State and Professional Initiatives

The McCormick Center for Early Childhood Leadership has partnered with professional development systems that link with quality rating and improvement systems across the country, institutions of higher education, and scholarship agencies that have identified ways that the Aim4Excellence online modules fit with current options for early childhood professionals. Click on states where we are recognized for more information!

Many states have utilized Aim4Excellence to support reinvigorating and rebuilding leadership capacity since the pandemic. Learn more by watching this BUILD Initiative webinar highlighting three state action plans and learn more about how we collaborate with states to provide exceptional workforce development to early childhood leaders by providing various delivery formats and online content focused on established leadership competencies.

Credentialed Directors List

More than 2,500 early childhood educators have enrolled in Aim4Excellence and more than 2,800 have earned their credential. The following individuals have successfully met all requirements to hold an active Aim4Excellence National Director Credential:
